    {
      "name": "1. Auth — Login",
      "description": "Single endpoint handles all auth flows — new user, profile setup, and returning user. token_id is always required. All other fields are optional. Flutter navigates based on isProfileComplete in the response.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check Account",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Account check succeeded', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(res.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.have.property('exists');",
                  "});",
                  "if (res.success && res.exists && res.data) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', res.data.refresh_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', String(res.data.user.id));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/check-account?token_id=mock_google_token",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "check-account"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "token_id",
                  "value": "mock_google_token",
                  "description": "Google ID token (supports 'mock_google_token' in development)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Checks if a user already exists in the database by verifying their Google ID token."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login / Profile Setup",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.data.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', res.data.refresh_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', String(res.data.user.id));",
                  "  pm.test('Request succeeded', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('Access token is a string', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.data.access_token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('is_new_user field present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res).to.have.property('is_new_user');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('is_profile_complete field present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.data.user).to.have.property('is_profile_complete');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('wallet in response', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.data.user).to.have.property('wallet');",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (res.data.user.is_profile_complete) {",
                  "    console.log('is_profile_complete: true → Flutter goes to Home Screen');",
                  "  } else {",
                  "    console.log('is_profile_complete: false → Flutter shows Profile Setup Screen');",
                  "  }",
                  "  console.log('is_new_user:', res.is_new_user);",
                  "  console.log('wallet:', res.data.user.wallet);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "token_id",
                  "value": "mock_google_token",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Google ID token (supports 'mock_google_token' in development)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "display_name",
                  "value": "John Doe",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional: User's name for setup"
                },
                {
                  "key": "gender",
                  "value": "male",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional: male/female/other"
                },
                {
                  "key": "country_name",
                  "value": "India",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional: Country name"
                },
                {
                  "key": "country_code",
                  "value": "IN",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional: 2-letter ISO country code"
                },
                {
                  "key": "email",
                  "value": "vajanirav2003@gmail.com",
                  "type": "text",
                  "description": "Optional: User's email"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "One API for all Flutter auth scenarios. token_id is always required. All other fields are optional.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nUSAGE GUIDE\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\nScenario A — Login Screen (new or returning):\nSend only token_id. Remove all other fields.\n→ New user:       is_profile_complete: false → show Profile Setup Screen\n→ Returning user: is_profile_complete: true  → go to Home Screen\n\nScenario B — Profile Setup Screen:\nSend token_id + display_name + gender + country_name + country_code.\n→ Backend saves profile, is_profile_complete: true → go to Home Screen\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nFLUTTER NAVIGATION RULE\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nif (res.data.user.is_profile_complete == false) → Profile Setup Screen\nif (res.data.user.is_profile_complete == true)  → Home Screen\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nEXPECTED RESPONSE\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"is_new_user\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Login successful\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"access_token\": \"eyJhbG...\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"eyJhbG...\",\n    \"expires_in\": 604800,\n    \"user\": {\n      \"id\": 1,\n      \"email\": \"nirav@gmail.com\",\n      \"display_name\": \"John Doe\",\n      \"photo_url\": \"https://...\",\n      \"gender\": \"male\",\n      \"country_name\": \"India\",\n      \"country_code\": \"IN\",\n      \"is_vip\": false,\n      \"is_online\": true,\n      \"is_profile_complete\": false,\n      \"wallet_balance\": 0,\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
