    {
      "name": "3. Video Calling",
      "description": "Video calling uses 1 HTTP route + 2 WebSocket namespaces.\n\nHTTP: GET /users/:id — loads partner info on call screen.\nWebSocket /matchmaking — finding, ringing, accepting, skipping.\nWebSocket /call — join room, WebRTC SDP/ICE relay, end or skip call.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Partner Info",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Partner info loaded', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.have.property('id');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Has display_name', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.have.property('display_name');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('No private fields exposed', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.not.have.property('email');",
                  "  pm.expect(res).to.not.have.property('google_id');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/users/{{partnerId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "users",
                "{{partnerId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Loads partner's public info (name, photo, country, gender) to show on the call screen overlay.\nSet the `partnerId` collection variable to the partner's user ID before running."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "⚡ WS /matchmaking — How To Connect",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://localhost:3001/matchmaking",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "3001",
              "path": [
                "matchmaking"
              ]
            },
            "description": "════ WEBSOCKET — NOT A REST API ════\n\nNamespace: /matchmaking\nHandles: finding users, ringing, accepting, declining, cancelling, skipping.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nHOW TO TEST IN POSTMAN\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n1. Click New → WebSocket Request\n2. URL: ws://localhost:3001/matchmaking\n3. Headers → add:  Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}\n4. Click Connect\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nEVENTS TO SEND: FLUTTER → BACKEND\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n► match:findUser  (User A clicks Connect button — no body)\n→ Backend picks a random available user (User B)\n→ User B receives ◄ match:incomingCall\n→ User A receives ◄ match:calling\n\n► match:acceptCall  (User B taps Accept)\n{ \"callId\": \"uuid\" }\n→ Both receive ◄ match:callAccepted with roomId\n\n► match:declineCall  (User B taps Decline)\n{ \"callId\": \"uuid\" }\n→ User A receives ◄ match:callDeclined\n\n► match:cancelCall  (User A cancels before B responds)\n{ \"callId\": \"uuid\" }\n→ User B popup dismissed ◄ match:callCancelled\n\n► match:next  (after call:skipConfirmed — find next user)\n(no body)\n→ Immediately finds another random user to ring\n\n► match:backToAvailable  (after call ends, re-enter pool)\n(no body)\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nEVENTS RECEIVED: BACKEND → FLUTTER\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n◄ match:incomingCall  (to callee User B)\n{\n  \"callId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"caller\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"displayName\": \"John\",\n    \"photoUrl\": \"https://...\",\n    \"bio\": \"...\",\n    \"gender\": \"male\",\n    \"country\": { \"name\": \"India\", \"code\": \"IN\" }\n  }\n}\n\n◄ match:calling  (to caller User A)\n{\n  \"callId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"calleeId\": 2\n}\n\n◄ match:callAccepted  (to BOTH users)\n{\n  \"roomId\": \"uuid-room-id\",\n  \"partnerId\": 2,\n  \"iceServers\": [\n    { \"urls\": \"stun:stun.l.google.com:19302\" },\n    { \"urls\": \"turn:...\", \"username\": \"meetzy\", \"credential\": \"...\" }\n  ]\n}\n→ Save roomId → connect to /call WebSocket\n\n◄ match:callDeclined   { \"message\": \"User declined your call\" }\n◄ match:callCancelled  { \"callId\": \"uuid\" }\n◄ match:callExpired    { \"message\": \"Call request expired or cancelled\" }\n◄ match:noUsersAvailable  { \"message\": \"No users are available right now.\" }\n◄ match:partnerLeft    { \"roomId\": \"uuid\" }  ← partner disconnected"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "⚡ WS /call — WebRTC Signaling",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "ws://localhost:3001/call",
              "protocol": "ws",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "3001",
              "path": [
                "call"
              ]
            },
            "description": "════ WEBSOCKET — NOT A REST API ════\n\nNamespace: /call\nHandles: joining a room, WebRTC SDP/ICE relay, ending or skipping a call.\nBackend does NOT process video — only relays SDP and ICE signals between peers.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nHOW TO TEST IN POSTMAN\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n1. Click New → WebSocket Request\n2. URL: ws://localhost:3001/call\n3. Headers → add:  Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}\n4. Click Connect\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nEVENTS TO SEND: FLUTTER → BACKEND\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n► call:join  (send immediately after match:callAccepted)\n{ \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\" }\n→ When both users joined:\n→ User A ◄ call:ready { isInitiator: true  } — creates SDP offer\n→ User B ◄ call:ready { isInitiator: false } — waits for offer\n\n► call:sdpOffer  (User A sends, isInitiator only)\n{\n  \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\",\n  \"sdp\": { \"type\": \"offer\", \"sdp\": \"v=0\\r\\no=- ...\" }\n}\n→ Relayed to User B  ◄ call:sdpOffer\n\n► call:sdpAnswer  (User B sends after receiving offer)\n{\n  \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\",\n  \"sdp\": { \"type\": \"answer\", \"sdp\": \"v=0\\r\\no=- ...\" }\n}\n→ Relayed to User A  ◄ call:sdpAnswer\n\n► call:iceCandidate  (both users send, multiple times)\n{\n  \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\",\n  \"candidate\": {\n    \"candidate\": \"candidate:123...\",\n    \"sdpMid\": \"0\",\n    \"sdpMLineIndex\": 0\n  }\n}\n→ Relayed to other user  ◄ call:iceCandidate\n→ WebRTC peer connected — video starts\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nENDING THE CALL\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n► call:end  (End Call button pressed)\n{ \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\" }\n→ BOTH users receive ◄ call:ended\n→ BOTH navigate to Home Screen\n→ Duration saved to MySQL\n→ No one is auto re-queued\n\n► call:skip  (Swipe right-to-left)\n{ \"roomId\": \"{{roomId}}\" }\n→ Skipped user  ◄ call:skipped  → goes to Home Screen\n→ Swiping user  ◄ call:skipConfirmed\n→ Swiping user then sends match:next on /matchmaking\n→ Backend rings another random user\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nEVENTS RECEIVED: BACKEND → FLUTTER\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n\n◄ call:ready\n{ \"roomId\": \"uuid\", \"isInitiator\": true }\n\n◄ call:sdpOffer   { \"from\": 1, \"sdp\": { ... } }\n◄ call:sdpAnswer  { \"from\": 2, \"sdp\": { ... } }\n◄ call:iceCandidate  { \"from\": 1, \"candidate\": { ... } }\n\n◄ call:ended\n{ \"by\": 1, \"roomId\": \"uuid\", \"reason\": \"ended_by_user\" }\n\n◄ call:skipped\n{ \"by\": 1, \"roomId\": \"uuid\", \"message\": \"Your partner skipped to the next user\" }\n\n◄ call:skipConfirmed\n{ \"roomId\": \"uuid\" }\n\n◄ call:error  { \"message\": \"Room not found\" }\n◄ call:ended  { \"by\": 1, \"roomId\": \"uuid\", \"reason\": \"partner_disconnected\" }\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────\nFULL SEQUENCE SUMMARY\n──────────────────────────────────────────\n1.  /matchmaking: A → match:findUser\n2.  /matchmaking: B ← match:incomingCall\n3.  /matchmaking: B → match:acceptCall\n4.  /matchmaking: Both ← match:callAccepted { roomId }\n5.  /call:        Both connect and → call:join { roomId }\n6.  /call:        A ← call:ready { isInitiator: true }\n               B ← call:ready { isInitiator: false }\n7.  /call:        A → call:sdpOffer\n8.  /call:        B ← call:sdpOffer\n9.  /call:        B → call:sdpAnswer\n10. /call:        A ← call:sdpAnswer\n11. /call:        Both ↔ call:iceCandidate (multiple)\n12. WebRTC connected — video starts\n\nEnd call:  → call:end   → both ← call:ended  → Home Screen\nSwipe next: → call:skip → skipped ← call:skipped → Home Screen\n                         swiping ← call:skipConfirmed\n                         swiping → match:next → rings next user"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
